Peristernia violacea is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae, the spindle snails, the tulip snails and their allies.  It is characterized by a silver or gold periostracum that is iridescent when wet, and a deep violet aperture.  It is likely endemic to the Line Islands, and is recorded from Palmyra, Kiritimati, and other nearby islands.